Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @Potatoes{450} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel!). Pop the wedges on a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and toss to coat. Scatter over the @Sesame Seeds{15} and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Spread them out in a single layer and roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

Chop the @Broccoli{1} into florets (like small trees!), halving any larger ones. Peel and grate the @Ginger{1/4}. Halve the @Lime{1}. Trim the @Spring Onion{1} then slice thinly.

In a small #jug{} or #bowl{}, combine the @Honey{15}, @Soy Sauce{25}, ginger and juice from half the lime.

Have ready a wide sheet of #foil{} for each @Cod Fillets{2}. Place one fillet in the middle of each sheet. Spoon the honey soy sauce equally over each fillet, making sure there is some ginger on each one then bring the sides of the foil up and scrunch up the edges to create a tight parcel. Pop these parcels onto a baking tray. Arrange the broccoli next to the parcels, drizzle with oil, salt and pepper.

> Remember to wash your hands after handling raw fish.

Bake the fish and broccoli until the broccoli is tender and crispy and the fish is just cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> The fish might be cooked after 12 minutes but if the broccoli needs longer then remove the fish parcels and pop the broccoli back in the oven.

> The fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

Pop a fish parcel on each plate, open them up and scatter over the sliced spring onion and squeeze over any remaining lime juice. Serve with the potato wedges and broccoli, enjoy!